What are the advantages of using Hibernate over JDBC?

Hibernate is a framework used in Java to ease the development of applications to 
interact with databases. On the other hand, 
JDBC is an API to connect and execute queries with database in Java.
 
 Avantage 
 1) data base dependency:-> hybernet not depend on the database while JDBC dependent on databse 
  to excute any operation.
  
 2) hebernet requre less number of code to excute any application  while Jdbc take large number of
   code to perform any operation.
   
 3) in hybernet framework no need to handle exception while the JDBC many times require the exception 
    handle
   
  
  
 
 